track.name: Mood Indigo
comments: Coolest cat around ,trumpet swee!t band smooth and delicioso!
Not quite sure which version I've been listening to. Remains a haunting tune.
I am not familiar with this version. Not one of the best.
There you go. In you go. Indigo. deep blue, dark cool. It's in his royal blood.
Duke Ellington. From the Old Guard. +reps.

Anyone able to tell me why the version lastFM plays me is a monster arrangement a good quarter of an hour long? Was it some special project? Or is it a very cunning piece of digital editing that actually runs parts of several versions together? It's good, just VERY unexpected when it looked like you were going to get a prewar 78rpm version ...
the earliest version is best by far. the one with the operatic singing over it kinda sucks.
amazing. makes me think that Brian Wilson had some Duke on the mind when he was writing SMiLE...
deep blue, dark cool. It's in his royal blood.
Great Duke is not surpassed the master of the genre!!!!!
More class in his pinky than most of today's pop stars will ever have.
Other jams may be as good, but none are better - IMHO. The version with Duke and Louie on the Masterworks Sessions is also sublime.
